==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Offtake
<hw>Off"take`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Off</ets> +
<ets>take</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Act of taking off; specif., the
taking off or purchase of goods.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Something taken off; a deduction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A channel for taking away air or water; also, the
point of beginning of such a channel; a take-off.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>off-the-cuff</ent>⟦br⟧
